  "body": "\n## Summary\nThis PR addresses the code review comment from Gemini Code Assist regarding error handling in the edit feed modal.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### Frontend Error Handling Fix\n- Modified `fetchData` helper function to re-throw errors instead of showing generic alerts and returning `null`\n- This allows the `handleEditFeedSubmit` function to properly catch and display specific error messages in the modal\n- Improves user experience by providing inline error feedback instead of generic alerts\n\n## Technical Details\n- **Before**: `fetchData` would catch all errors, show an alert, and return `null`, making the `else` block in `handleEditFeedSubmit` unreachable\n- **After**: `fetchData` re-throws errors, allowing `handleEditFeedSubmit` to catch them and display specific error messages in the modal UI\n\n## Verification\n- All tests continue to pass (74 passed, 1 skipped)\n- Error handling in the edit feed modal now works as intended\n- Users will see specific error messages in the modal instead of generic alerts\n\nThis completes the code review cycle for the editable feed URLs feature by fixing the error handling issue identified in the previous review.\n",
